data.chText: 新职员；新生；新会员；新成员
data.enText: a person who has recently joined a profession, university, etc.

data.chText: 新加入警察部队的女警察
data.enText: new women entrants to the police force
a person or an animal that enters a race or a competition; a person that enters an exam

tr: a commodity that enters competition with established merchandise
example: a well publicized entrant is the pocket computer
new entrants to the country must go though immigration procedures

tr: any new participant in some activity

value.def: An entrant is a person who has recently become a member of an institution such as a university.
An entrant is a person who is taking part in a competition.

example.ex: All items entered for the competition must be the entrant's own work.
example.tran: 所有参赛作品必须是参赛者本人的作品。
